Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamics properties, VLE and HE, of the systems 2-pentanol and cyclohexane or methylbenzene for contributing to the knowledge of new biofuels
Citation.sAbstract: Accurate experimental data of vapour-liquid equilibria (VLE) and excess enthalpies (HE) are reported for the binary systems (2-pentanol + cyclohexane) and (2-pentanol + methylbenzene). An isothermal total pressure cell was used for measuring the VLE at T = 313.15 K. The data were correlated using Margules, Wilson, NRTL and UNIQUAC equations. The excess enthalpies were measured at two different temperatures T = (298.15 and 313.15) K using an isothermal flow calorimeter and were correlated by the Redlich-Kister equation. The binary system 2-pentanol + methylbenzene exhibits an azeotrope and both systems present a positive deviation from the ideality. Furthermore, an endothermic behaviour is observed when 2-pentanol is mixed with these hydrocarbons.
